Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams}(chopped into 2cm chunks) into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Halve and peel the @red onion{1}(halved and peeled), then cut each half into 3 wedges.

Pop the potato chunks and onion wedges onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, sprinkle over half the @smoked paprika{1/2%sachet}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer. 

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, pop the @British Cumberland sausages{8} onto another baking tray. Bake on the middle shelf until golden brown and cooked through, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. They're cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When the sausages have ~{5%minutes} of roasting time remaining, add the @peas{120%grams} to the tray, drizzle with a little @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Return to the oven for the remaining cook time.

Meanwhile, pop a #small saucepan{} on medium-high heat. Stir in the @tomato passata{1%carton}, @chicken stock paste{10%grams}, remaining smoked paprika and half of the @honey{1%tbsp}. Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat. Cover with a #lid{} and simmer until slightly thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

When everything's ready, share the sausages and peas between your plates. Serve the roasted veg alongside, then spoon over the bravas sauce and drizzle on the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}. Drizzle the remaining honey over the sausages to finish. Enjoy!